  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (v0.5 synthetic)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The hemolysis accumulation model applies the power-law stress-exposure relation (Giersiepen-Wurzinger formulation), which assumes a linear superposition of scalar shear-stress damage contributions along Lagrangian pathlines. This linearity assumption is treated as broadly applicable across rotary blood pump geometries; the package does not include a dedicated validation activity confirming that linear damage superposition holds under the recirculating, unsteady flow regimes characteristic of the CPB operating envelope.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-rh-less-than-1",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-giersiepen-wurzinger",
