    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not-assessed per MRL 2 scoping rules. NIH predictions agree with FDA benchmark in-vitro data within 11% across all operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model is accepted on the basis of its established regulatory precedent and the stated broad applicability of the linear damage superposition assumption; no additional verification of this theoretical precondition against CPB-specific recirculating flow conditions was deemed necessary by the team. Overall credibility assessment supports regulatory submission for the Class II CPB device.",
